## Phase 1: CLI Core and Configuration

* [ ] Set up clap for CLI routing (yoru init, yoru build, yoru deploy).
* [ ] Build yoru init to scaffold projects from templates (tweak, tool, cyanide).
* [ ] Generate default layout directories (src/, layout/) and a boilerplate Yoru.toml.
* [ ] Implement TOML parser using serde to extract build metadata and target settings.

## Phase 2: Logos Integration and Compiler Bridge

* [ ] Build preprocessor to pass .x and .xm files through the Logos engine.
* [ ] Dump intermediate .m and .mm files into a hidden build folder (.yoru/build/).
* [ ] Configure compiler runner to handle target triples (aarch64-apple-ios).
* [ ] Inject clang flags for arm64e PAC support.
* [ ] Implement parallel file compilation to speed up build times over Theos.

## Phase 3: Cross-Platform Packaging and Signing

* [ ] Integrate xtool for cross-platform ad-hoc signing and entitlement injection.
* [ ] Build file layout mapper:
* Rootless: Route binaries to /var/jb/ Library paths.
* Rootful: Route binaries to traditional root paths for iOS < 12 compatibility.
* RootHide: Add hooks for randomized jbroot translation layout.


* [ ] Create native .deb archiver that builds control and data tarballs directly.
* [ ] Auto-generate Debian control files using values parsed from Yoru.toml.

## Phase 4: vphone-cli and Deployment Workflow

* [ ] Build a bridge to detect local running instances of vphone-cli.
* [ ] Automate pushing and installing the compiled .deb directly into the active VM container.
* [ ] Implement yoru deploy using an SSH client (ssh2 crate) for physical device transfers.
* [ ] Automate post-install steps (killall -9 SpringBoard / respring).
* [ ] Add hot reloading using the notify crate to recompile, package, and deploy on file save.

## Phase 5: Cyanide Implementation

* [ ] Map out Cyanide out-of-process APIs and implement Rust bindings for the remote Objective-C bridge.
* [ ] Add a dedicated Cyanide workspace template to the yoru init command.

